title.narrative: GEF26-5 corridors restored or established in critical ecosystems or sensitive areas in the production landscape
Monitoring shows improvement in ecosystem biodiversity (for habitats of globally important biodiversity indicator species) and presence of indicator spp in production landscape in intervention areas

target.value: Increased connectivity within 5 critical ecosystems through corridors established or restored. Indicator spp monitored in total 5ecosystems.

title.narrative: Increase in number of hectares under improved or alternative management for biodiversity (small and medium <1000 ha)
Increase in number of hectares under improved management for biodiversity (large producers) as determined by technology transfer program criteria
Ecoregional planning tools identify priority biodiversity areas in the production landscape and are recognized in the forestry promotion systems at national and provincial levels

baseline.value: Biodiversity and production visions developed for Patagonia and Mesopotamia not integrated into forestry planning and management

target.value: Maps adopted and in use, and results incorporated into draft resolutions, in 7 provinces and federal government

title.narrative: At least 3 provinces establish or elaborate draft forest policies regulatory framework or promotion programs with consideration to biodiversity

baseline.value: No provincial forest and biodiversity policy, regulatory framework or promotion programs

target.value: 3 draft documents discussed and final versions elaborated

title.narrative: New Forestry policies, regulatory frameworks, and/or promotion programs incorporate biodiversity conservation and sustainable use concepts at the federal level and in at least 3 provinces.

baseline.value: no new policies, regulatory frameworks, and/or promotion programs incorporate biodiversity conservation

target.value: new policies, regulatory frameworks, and/or promotion programs incorporate biodiversity conservation

title.narrative: GEF17-Extension programs incorporating biodiversity into forestry technical assistance developed and implemented in 7 provinces
GEF24-Baseline studies prepared and dialogue advanced for establishment 7 of private and public protected areas within targeted eco-regions in the plantation forestry landscape
GEF16-Subregional international conference held in Argentina on Plantations and Biodiversity for global dissemination of lessons
GEF25-Increases in locales identified for private and public protected areas for biodiversity conservation as result of improved dialogueand governance in the forestry sector
GEF21-Technical assistance for small and medium producers in agroforestry (Misiones) or best management practices (Patagonia and Mesopotamia) benefits 20,000 ha

actual.value: 13,000 has (504 producers and their families benefitted)

title.narrative: GEF18-Improved knowledge base for improvement of ecosystem conditions and reduction of threats to species of global importance through special treatments via pilot initiatives
GEF20-No. of nurseries offering native tree seedlings increases by 100%
GEF19-Complete draft program curriculum for certificate in biodiversity and plantations. Developed and adopted in at least 1 regional school in each of Mesopotamia and Patagonia

actual.value: program curriculum in progress for 5 institutions

title.narrative: GEF14-Toolkits developed and disseminated for grasslands, forest and wetland ecosystems (5)

target.value: 5 toolkits developed and disseminated to a cumulative total of 3500 producers

title.narrative: GEF4-Designated national authorities completed and applying EIA training
GEF13-Seed bank (natives) networks established in Misiones, Delta and Patagonia
GEF9-5 of 7 provincial environmental agencies employ stronger biodiversity criteria in Environmental Impact Assessment
GEF1-Biodiversity planning and monitoring tools developed
GEF12-Economic analyses developed for plantations and biodiversity in all 7 provinces involved in the project
GEF15-Pilot projects for dissemination of best practices for biodiversity completed for 7 provinces
GEF10-Draft federal legislation and associated regulatory framework incorporating appropriate diversity concerns developed and presented for promulgation and adoption
GEF2-Percentage of designated Dirección Forestal officials trained in biodiversity and plantations
GEF27-SAGPyA Coordination Team is organized formally and successfully managing project
GEF28-Monitoring programs in place and providing date to relevant national programs
GEF3-Percentage of designated pertinent officials trained in biodiversity and plantations
GEF6-Participating extension agents trained and applying knowledge on best practices in field
GEF5-Designated provincial authorities completed and applying SEA and EIA training
GEF7-Provincial forestry offices equipped for biodiversity databases and sustainable management
GEF8-Draft policies,regulation and/or promotion programs developed and consulted with stakeholders
GEF23-50,000 ha of large plantations (>1,000 ha) are incorporating biodiversity- responsible practices and planning within ecoregions of global importance through project
GEF11-The Advisory Commission for law 25,080 (or its successor) regularly incorporates, by EOP, biodiversity-related subjects in its agenda

target.value: Biodiversity is included as a topic in more than one regular meeting of the Advisory Commission (or successor)

actual.value: Biodiversity is included in regular meetings

title.narrative: GEF22-Environmental education increases awareness of plantations and on biodiversity in sampled subproject areas by 50% over baseline
Strategic Environmental Assessments, guidelines and strategies for the sustainable use and conservation of forests available and inuse

actual.value: Strategic Environmental Assessments are being prepared for NOA region (BIRF) and Mesopotamia and Patagonia (GEF: see indicator1-GEF)
